ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Identifies original RCT subject enrolled in
Total number of client utterances in session
Frequency of client utterances coded as pertaining to reinforcing value of target behavior
Frequency of client utterances coded as pertaining to reinforcing value of alternative behaviors
Frequency of client utterances coded as pertaining to reinforcing value of independent behaviors
Frequency of client utterances coded as non-relevant
Frequency of client utterances coded as past temporality
Frequency of client utterances coded as present temporality
Frequency of client utterances coded as future temporality
Frequency of client utterances coded in the approach direction
Frequency of client utterances coded in the neutral direction
Frequency of client utterances coded in the avoid direction
Frequency of client utterances coded as avoid target behavior
Notes: Behavioral domain and motivational direction are coded independently for each utterance. This element identifies utterances coded as both target behavior and avoid direction

ElementDescription: Frequency of client utterances coded as approach target behavior
Notes: Behavioral domain and motivational direction are coded independently for each utterance. This element identifies utterances coded as both target behavior and approach direction

ElementDescription: Frequency of client utterances coded as avoid alternative behaviors
Notes: Behavioral domain and motivational direction are coded independently for each utterance. This element identifies utterances coded as both alternative behavior and avoid direction

ElementDescription: Frequency of client utterances coded as approach alternative behaviors
Notes: Behavioral domain and motivational direction are coded independently for each utterance. This element identifies utterances coded as both alternative behavior and approach direction
